{
  "texts": [
    "Academic integrity: What measures should be in place to verify that AI-generated content has not been misrepresented as human-authored?",
    "Authorial authenticity: How can researchers distinguish between AI-generated and human-generated content in academic submissions?",
    "The role of generative AI in academic publication: Should AI-generated content be explicitly labeled in academic publications, and if so, how? In that matter, scientific journals such as Nature (2024) foot_0 have established guidelines regarding the relationship between AI-generated content and authorship.",
    "Afterward, more and more publishers and journals declared their own policies regarding the usage of generative AI in the process of writing (Elsevier 2024 foot_1; Taylor & Francis 2024 foot_2; Sage 2024 foot_3 …).",
    "However, as these guidelines are present, there is no structured consensus-based guideline development (Ganjavi et al. 2024)."
  ]
}